CatDescriptText: Mrs. Elizabeth M. Smith, 7425 Frankstown Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 28, 1957, pg.3 with question: "Do you think Pennsylvania's 'blue laws' against 'unnecessary' Sunday sales should be enforced?" answer reads: "Yes, everything should be closed-up because it's Sunday."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Elizabeth M. Smith, wearing light colored head scarf and plaid coat, holding paper bag and handbag, standing in front of light colored marble pillar between store windows, one on left with stocking display and sign that reads "You are sure to please her with an Emma Jettick Gift Certificate", and one on right with female mannequin wearing dress
